# Cloudflare Pages redirects — the /network/<id> re-root + the stories layer.
#
# The live site (Lima) was rooted at /bosc; it now lives at /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co
# so future watershed sites are clean siblings, and its investigation is a *story* beneath it at
# /stories/project-bosc (the guided walk; chapters flattened). These keep every old, deployed URL
# working. The network root `/` is a TEMPORARY (302), not permanent — it'll host real network
# content once warranted, so browsers must not hard-cache it.
#
# NETWORK-GLOBAL pages stay at the root and are NOT rewritten — /about, /about-me, /wiki/*, /ask,
# /directory/*, /submit (the network-tier lead form), and the API (/api/*).
#
# IMPORTANT — on Cloudflare Pages a redirect ALWAYS fires before a matching static asset. So a
# broad `/<x>/*` rule shadows real files under that path. Consequences encoded in the order below:
#  - NO `/submit` rule: it's a real network-tier page; a redirect would make it unreachable.
#  - `/walk/crops/*` is a 200 passthrough BEFORE `/walk/*` (teardown source-card crops live at
#    public/walk/crops, served at /walk/crops — see teardowns.ts).
#  - the live site now lives UNDER /network, so the old broad `/network/* -> /directory` rule was
#    REMOVED (it would shadow /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/*); only the exact /network
#    hub redirect remains. Story-specific /bosc rules come BEFORE the generic /bosc/*.

/                       /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/                                301

# Teardown crops — serve as-is before any /walk redirect.
/walk/crops/*           /walk/crops/:splat                                                     200

# /bosc -> /network/<id>, and the story moved to /stories/project-bosc (chapters flattened).
/bosc/start             /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/stories/project-bosc            301
/bosc/intro             /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/stories/project-bosc            301
/bosc/walk              /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/stories/project-bosc/contents   301
/bosc/walk/*            /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/stories/project-bosc/:splat     301
/bosc                   /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/                                301
/bosc/*                 /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/:splat                          301

# Even-older root-level legacy URLs (pre-/bosc) — straight to the new paths.
/start                  /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/stories/project-bosc            301
/timeline               /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/timeline                        301
/site/*                 /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/site/:splat                     301
/watershed/*            /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/watershed/:splat                301
/docs/*                 /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/docs/:splat                     301
/reports/*              /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/reports/:splat                  301
/walk/*                 /network/american-sugar-creek-allen-co/stories/project-bosc/:splat     301

# The network hub moved /network -> /directory (#402); keep the exact old hub URLs working. The
# broad /network/* rule is intentionally gone — /network/<slug> is now real per-site content.
/network                /directory/                                                            301
/network/hypotheses     /directory/hypotheses                                                  301
